CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 14, 1950, pg. 10 reads: "Luncheon Speaker - Mrs. Sallie Nuby Edwards, grand basileus of Sigma Gamma Rho Sorority of St. Louis, Mo., is pictured addressing a luncheon meeting last Thursday afternoon at Dutch Henry's Restaurant. The event was in honor of the late Dr. Gerorge Washington Carver.  To her left is Mrs. Marie Saul of the Carver Week committee and Dr. Lawrence Van Kirk, who served as master of ceremonies. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group of men and women, including Sallie Nuby Edwards, standing at microphone, and Dr. Lawrence Van Kirk seated to left, and Marie Saul wearing striped suit jacket, seated at table for Carver Week luncheon, in Dutch Henry's Restaurant
